# Build Workflow Standards

## Development Workflow

When creating or editing components, always follow this sequence:

### 1. Edit Source
```bash
code packages/_redhorn-components/src/components/Button/Button.lite.tsx
```

### 2. Generate All Frameworks
```bash
npm run build:mitosis
```

This generates:
- React (packages/react/)
- Angular (packages/angular/)
- Vue (packages/vue/)
- React Native (packages/react-native/)

### 3. Preview in Storybook
```bash
npm run storybook
```

### 4. Verify All Outputs

Check generated files look correct:
- `packages/react/src/components/ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx`
- `packages/angular/src/components/ComponentName/ComponentName.ts`
- `packages/vue/src/components/ComponentName/ComponentName.vue`
- `packages/react-native/src/components/ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx`

## Never Edit Generated Files

**❌ NEVER edit these directly:**
- `packages/react/src/components/**/*` (generated)
- `packages/angular/src/components/**/*` (generated)
- `packages/vue/src/components/**/*` (generated)
- `packages/react-native/src/components/**/*` (generated)

**✅ ALWAYS edit the source:**
- `packages/_redhorn-components/src/components/**/*.lite.tsx`

Changes in generated files will be overwritten on next build.

## Build Commands

- `npm run build:tokens` - Build design tokens only
- `npm run build:mitosis` - Generate framework components
- `npm run build:all` - Build tokens + generate components
- `npm run storybook` - Preview components

## Publishing Workflow

1. Create changeset: `npx changeset`
2. Select ALL packages: tokens, react, angular, react-native, vue
3. Apply versions: `npm run version`
4. Publish: `npm run publish:all`

All packages MUST version together (synchronized versions).
